FlorML is an XML schema for marking up legacy and modern taxonomic works, such 
as floras and faunas.

================================================================================

AVAILABILITY:
FlorML can be downloaded from these two Github repos:
https://github.com/thoha/FlorML (preferred, most up-to-date)
https://github.com/naturalis/FlorML

================================================================================

DOCUMENTATION:
Documentation is available in the "Documentation"-folder in the repository. 
Basic instructions are included in the XML schema, and in the README files for 
each of the Perl script archives.

================================================================================

AUTHORS:
Thomas Hamann
Andreas Müller

================================================================================

CITATION:
Please cite this work appropriately:

Hamann, T., Müller, A., Roos, M.C., Sosef, M. & E. Smets. Detailed mark-up of 
semi-monographic legacy taxonomic works using FlorML. 2014. Taxon 63 (2): 377-393. 

